<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="842" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12612.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Brazilian Minister, Mexico City, telegraphs under yesterday’s date
                            President Carbajal has appointed as delegates General Lauro Villar,
                            Chief Justice of the Supreme Military Court, and Licenciado David
                            Gutiérrez Allende, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Mexico, who
                            will leave Mexico City today accompanied by one secretary.</p>
                        <p>Convey the above to General Carranza, and request that full protection be
                            extended to the delegates, and that their transportation be
                            facilitated.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>